<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="287" pageId="9" pageNumber="286" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1806,2013]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="287" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,256,1807,1833]" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">Remark.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[317,365,1807,1833]" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">type</typeStatus>
locality ‘Pe Yen Tsin’ is now called Shiyang Town (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[970,1054,1808,1831]" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">Ƃŧẘ</emphasis>
) of Dayao County (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1287,1371,1808,1831]" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">Ęďss</emphasis>
), and formerly called Baiyanjing (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[480,563,1844,1867]" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">àü#</emphasis>
) of Yanfeng County (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[823,907,1844,1867]" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">üƚss</emphasis>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ren, G. - D. &amp; Xu, J. - S." box="[933,1147,1842,1869]" pageId="9" pageNumber="286" pagination="23 - 34" refId="ref11188" refString="Ren, G. - D. &amp; Xu, J. - S. (2011) The genus Hexarhopalus Fairmaire, 1891 in China, with description of three new species (Coleoptera, Tenebrionidae, Cnodalonini), Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 57, 23 - 34." type="journal article" year="2011">Ren and Xu, 2011</bibRefCitation>
identified the specimens from Ailao Mountain (
<collectingRegion box="[407,603,1878,1905]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
) as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[651,988,1878,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuatus" subGenus="Hexarhopalus">
<emphasis box="[651,809,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">Hexarhopalus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[826,854,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[871,988,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="286">attenuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, we examined the specimens from the same locality, and the different characters suggest that specimens from Ailao Mountain is a new species. Although they are similar in general appearance, and both possess three longitudinal grooves on pronotum. But they can be easily separated from each other, the new species with shoulders fully developed (shouldersless in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[151,487,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuatus" subGenus="Hexarhopalus">
<emphasis box="[151,309,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="287">Hexarhopalus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[326,354,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="287">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[370,487,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="287">attenuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and except the lateral one, other two grooves of pronotum are much weak (deep in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[151,486,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hexarhopalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuatus" subGenus="Hexarhopalus">
<emphasis box="[151,309,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="287">Hexarhopalus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[326,353,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="287">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[369,486,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="287">attenuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
